UMCS.util
Class CompressedTrie

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--UMCS.util.CompressedTrie
All Implemented Interfaces:
Trie
public class CompressedTrie
extends java.lang.Object
implements Trie

Compressed implementation of the Abstract Datatype Trie. Strings are stored in lexicographical order so all enumerations are sorted. This implementation keeps a singly linked list of all positions.

Author:
Jeroen Donkers

Constructor Detail

CompressedTrie

public CompressedTrie()
Create an empty Compressed Trie. For example: 
   Trie t = new CompressedTrie();
   t.insert("Computer");
   t.insert("Cooperation");
   t.insert("Apple");
   t.insert("Comsumer");
   TrieEnumerator te = t.findPrefix("co");

insert

public TriePos insert(java.lang.String v,
                      java.lang.Object c)
Description copied from interface: Trie
Insert a string into the Trie, and link a content object to this string. If the string is already present, the new content is rejected. If c is null, it is replaced by the NILL content. The function returns a reference to the newly added position.

Specified by:
insert in interface Trie
Parameters:
v - The string that is to be stored.
c - The object that is to be stored at the position of v.
Returns:
The position of the new string, if inserted, else null.
